{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904738229,"sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:33","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git add src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo && git commit -m \"Fix taxon constraint violations in epiphyseal tract and adductor muscle of hip\n\n- UBERON:0034714 (epiphyseal tract): Changed logical definition from\n  'innervates some parietal organ' to 'innervates some pineal complex',\n  and updated text definition accordingly. The pineal tract is a\n  branch of the epiphyseal tract and innervates the pineal body,\n  so the epiphyseal tract innervates more than just the parietal organ.\n  Fixes unsatisfiable FMA:77600.\n\n- UBERON:0011144 (adductor muscle of hip): Removed the\n  'innervated_by some obturator nerve' subclass axiom. The obturator\n  nerve is tetrapod-specific, but the logical definition of this term\n  (adductor muscle and part_of some pelvic complex) applies to all\n  vertebrates. The tight classification was causing teleost terms\n  (ZFA:0000497, ZFA:0000592) mapped to this hierarchy to become\n  unsatisfiable.\n\nCloses #3596\n\n@dragon-ai-agent\"","description":"Commit ontology changes"},"output":"[scribe-v1-ai4curation-uberon-agent-config-v3-.-togetherai-moonshotai-Kimi-K2.6-iter1-issue-3596 6a37d8c] Fix taxon constraint violations in epiphyseal tract and adductor muscle of hip\n 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n","metadata":{"output":"[scribe-v1-ai4curation-uberon-agent-config-v3-.-togetherai-moonshotai-Kimi-K2.6-iter1-issue-3596 6a37d8c] Fix taxon constraint violations in epiphyseal tract and adductor muscle of hip\n 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n","exit":0,"description":"Commit ontology changes","truncated":false},"title":"Commit ontology changes","time":{"start":1778904738224,"end":1778904738228}},"id":"prt_e2efc12b3001fum5wU1p9YIQbS","sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","messageID":"msg_e2efc0f82001dPU1w