{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904755352,"sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:35","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","content":"Thank you for the detailed analysis in this issue.\n\nI have implemented the proposed fixes in PR #<NN>:\n\n1. **UBERON:0034714 (epiphyseal tract)**: The logical definition was revised from `innervates some parietal organ` to `innervates some pineal complex`, and the text definition was updated accordingly. This resolves the unsatisfiability of FMA:77600, since the pineal tract (a branch of the epiphyseal tract) innervates the pineal body, meaning the entire epiphyseal tract innervates more than just the parietal organ.\n\n2. **UBERON:0011144 (adductor muscle of hip)**: The `innervated_by some obturator nerve` subclass axiom was removed. This axiom was causing teleost terms mapped under this hierarchy (ZFA:0000497, ZFA:0000592) to become unsatisfiable, because the logical definition of `adductor muscle of hip` applies broadly to all vertebrates, while the obturator nerve is tetrapod-specific. Following the ontology's cross-species design philosophy, the broad definition was retained and the overly restrictive classification was removed.\n\nBoth terms now include a `term_tracker_item` linking back to this issue.\n\nPlease review when you have a chance — in particular, @gouttegd, your confirmation that option (B) (broad definition, no obturator nerve restriction) was the intended resolution would be appreciated.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904755346,"end":1778904755351}},"id":"prt_e2efc43b3001Y9OFAfgmvu134r","sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","messageID":"msg_e2efc395f001yPfzwrU00f7KNW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904773617,"sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:36","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","content":"## Summary\n\nThis PR fixes taxon constraint violations that were causing three imported terms to be unsatisfiable:\n- FMA:77600\n- ZFA:0000497\n- ZFA:0000592\n\n## Changes\n\n### UBERON:0034714 — epiphyseal tract\n\n**Problem**: The logical definition `EquivalentTo 'cranial neuron projection bundle' and (innervates some 'parietal organ')` was too narrow. The pineal tract (UBERON:0034715, xref FMA:77600) is a branching part of the epiphyseal tract and innervates the pineal body, which is part of the pineal complex but distinct from the parietal organ. This meant the epiphyseal tract innervated more than just the parietal organ, making the equivalence axiom inconsistent.\n\n**Fix**:\n- Text definition updated from \"A cranial nerve fiber tract that innervates the parietal eye.\" to \"A cranial nerve fiber tract that innervates the pineal complex.\"\n- Logical definition updated: `intersection_of: innervates UBERON:0015238 ! pineal complex` (was UBERON:0004869 ! parietal organ)\n- Added `term_tracker_item` linking to issue #3596\n\n### UBERON:0011144 — adductor muscle of hip\n\n**Problem**: This term exhibited a \"loose definition, tight classification\" pattern. Its logical definition (`EquivalentTo 'adductor muscle' and (part_of some 'pelvic complex')`) applies to all vertebrates. However, it was explicitly classified as `innervated_by some 'obturator nerve'`, which is tetrapod-specific. This caused teleost-specific subclasses (including those mapped to ZFA:0000497 and ZFA:0000592) to inherit tetrapod-only constraints and become unsatisfiable.\n\n**Fix**:\n- Removed the `relationship: innervated_by UBERON:0005465 ! obturator nerve` axiom\n- Added `term_tracker_item` linking to issue #3596\n- The logical definition was preserved to maintain broad vertebrate applicability\n\n## Rationale\n\nI chose **option (B)** for the adductor muscle of hip (broad definition, remove tight tetrapod-specific classification) because it is consistent with UBERON's design goal of being a cross-species anatomy ontology. Removing the obturator nerve innervation constraint allows the term to correctly group homologous structures across vertebrates without forcing teleost terms into an unsatisfiable state.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] Checked out terms using `obo-checkout.pl`\n- [x] Modified UBERON:0034714 text definition and logical definition\n- [x] Removed tetrapod-specific `innervated_by` axiom from UBERON:0011144\n- [x] Added `term_tracker_item` to both modified terms\n- [x] Checked in terms using `obo-checkin.pl`\n- [x] Verified changes in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` via git diff\n- [x] Committed changes\n\n## Notes\n\n`robot convert` was not available in this environment to reserialize the edit file, so the commit relies on the serialization produced by `obo-checkin.pl`.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904773610,"end":1778904773616}},"id":"prt_e2efc6d22001gJ3kp4dfwID8bR","sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","messageID":"msg_e2efc395f001yPfzwrU00f7KNW"}}
