{"type":"text","timestamp":1778904800202,"sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","part":{"id":"prt_e2efcebba001LdGy6SvsPEOrxf","messageID":"msg_e2efcddba0013A3sCUT80O257l","sessionID":"ses_1d1077240ffev4VS3hgbSpMyL5","type":"text","text":"I have completed the work for issue #3596. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Committed Changes\n- **UBERON:0034714 (epiphyseal tract)**: \n  - Updated text definition from \"innervates the parietal eye\" to \"innervates the pineal complex\"\n  - Changed logical definition from `innervates some parietal organ` to `innervates some pineal complex`\n  - This fixes the unsatisfiable FMA:77600, since the pineal tract is a branch of the epiphyseal tract and innervates the pineal body\n\n- **UBERON:0011144 (adductor muscle of hip)**:\n  - Removed the `innervated_by some obturator nerve` subclass axiom\n  - This was causing teleost terms (ZFA:0000497, ZFA:0000592) to become unsatisfiable because the obturator nerve is tetrapod-specific, while the logical definition applies to all vertebrates\n  - Kept the broad cross-species logical definition\n\n- Added `term_tracker_item` properties to both modified terms linking back to issue #3596\n\n## Files Created\n- `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md`: Terse update for the GitHub issue thread\n- `PR_COMMENTS.md`: Detailed description of the changes and rationale\n\nThe commit is on the branch you provided and is ready for you to push or further process.","time":{"start":1778904787898,"end":1778904800200}}}
